YNet was running a story on how to use your computer as an alarm clock. Here&rsquo;s what I do, for our commandline junkies :)
Here&rsquo;s ~/bin/run_alarm.sh:
#!/bin/bash find ~/music/ -name &#39;*.mp3&#39; -print0 | xargs -0 mplayer -shuffle &amp; MAXVOL=31 TIME=900 for (( i = 0; i &lt;= $MAXVOL; i++ )); do amixer set Master $i &gt; /dev/null; sleep `echo $TIME / $MAXVOL | bc -l` done This basically plays all of my MP3 files, in random order.

